cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV. 

The paper is about interpretability of neural retrieval models (NRMs) in information retrieval (IR), which is a subfield of computer science. Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the usage of neural networks, which falls under cs.CL (computational linguistics) and cs.CV (computer vision). The paper also discusses the ML community's approaches for explaining decisions made by deep neural networks, which falls under cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence).
